━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

LOCATION: Network Junction, Deck 2
STATUS: Infrastructure Mode
ACCESS: GRANTED - ENGINEERING PROTOCOLS ACTIVE

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Cables snake across the floor like frozen lightning. The Network Junction
is the physical heart of Helios Station's connectivity - where virtual
networks are born and traffic flows are shaped. Rows of switches hum
quietly, their port LEDs blinking in patterns that tell stories of data
in motion.

Network Architect Santos designed this infrastructure. Her diagrams cover
an entire wall, showing how Docker containers are organized into isolated
networks. "Networks aren't just connections," she always said. "They're
boundaries. They're architecture. They're security."

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │                                                                     │
    │  NEXUS: This is where infrastructure meets intention, Specialist.  │
    │                                                                     │
    │         Docker's networking model gives us power that physical     │
    │         networks can only dream of. We can create, destroy, and    │
    │         reshape network topologies in seconds.                     │
    │                                                                     │
    │         Architect Santos understood that network design is about   │
    │         more than connectivity - it's about control. Who can       │
    │         reach what. How traffic flows. Where boundaries lie.       │
    │                                                                     │
    │         You will learn to:                                         │
    │                                                                     │
    │         • Understand Docker bridge networking                      │
    │         • Create and configure custom networks                     │
    │         • Connect containers to multiple networks                  │
    │                                                                     │
    │         These skills will let you architect the station's future.  │
    │                                                                     │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

DOCKER NETWORK TYPES
════════════════════

    ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  TYPE        │  DESCRIPTION                  │  USE CASE          │
    ├──────────────┼───────────────────────────────┼────────────────────┤
    │  bridge      │  Isolated virtual network     │  Most containers   │
    │  host        │  Share host network stack     │  Performance       │
    │  none        │  No networking                │  Maximum isolation │
    │  overlay     │  Multi-host networking        │  Swarm clusters    │
    │  macvlan     │  Assign MAC addresses         │  Legacy apps       │
    └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

MODULE MISSIONS
═══════════════

    [1] bridge-explore   Understand Docker Bridge Networks
    [2] custom-nets      Create Custom Network Topologies
    [3] multi-network    Connect Containers Across Networks

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SKILLS YOU WILL LEARN
═════════════════════

    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  COMMAND                      │  PURPOSE                           │
    ├───────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────┤
    │  docker network ls            │  List all networks                 │
    │  docker network inspect       │  Show network details              │
    │  docker network create        │  Create new network                │
    │  docker network connect       │  Attach container to network       │
    │  docker network disconnect    │  Detach container from network     │
    │  docker inspect <container>   │  View container network config     │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

